s holding governments of immigrant destinations accountable at the local level. The potential for a functional immigrant worker rights regime, therefore, advocates to imagine a portable, universal system of justice and human rights, while simultaneously leaning on the bureaucratic minutiae of local enforcement. Taking Mexico and the United States as entry points, Scaling Migrant Worker Rights analyzes how an array of organizations put tactical pressure on government bureaucracies to holistically defend migrant rights. The result is a nuanced, multilayered picture of the impediments to and potential realization of migrant worker rights.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aLAW / Labor & Employment.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023 Englishz978311131914808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023z9783111318226oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831107913410 cprintz978052038445340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520384460?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520384460zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520384460/original  a978-3-11-079134-1 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131914-8 EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPL